# AI Employee - Silver Tier Environment Setup

## Environment Variables Template

Copy this file to `.env` and fill in your credentials.

```bash
# ===========================================
# AI Employee Silver Tier - Environment Setup
# ===========================================

# -------------------------------------------
# Gmail API Configuration
# -------------------------------------------
# 1. Visit: https://developers.google.com/gmail/api/quickstart/python
# 2. Click "Enable the Gmail API"
# 3. Download credentials.json and place in scripts/ folder
# 4. First run will require OAuth authorization

GMAIL_CREDENTIALS_PATH=./credentials.json
GMAIL_TOKEN_PATH=./token.json

# -------------------------------------------
# WhatsApp Web Configuration
# -------------------------------------------
# Session will be created automatically on first run
# QR code scan required for authentication

WHATSAPP_SESSION_PATH=./whatsapp_session

# -------------------------------------------
# Email MCP Server (SMTP)
# -------------------------------------------
# For Gmail:
# 1. Enable 2FA on your Google Account
# 2. Create App Password: https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
# 3. Use the App Password (not your regular password)

SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=587
SMTP_USER=your-email@gmail.com
SMTP_PASS=your-app-password-here

# For other providers:
# SMTP_HOST=smtp.office365.com
# SMTP_PORT=587

# -------------------------------------------
# LinkedIn MCP Server
# -------------------------------------------
# 1. Create app: https://www.linkedin.com/developers/apps
# 2. Get access token from your app
# 3. Get your person URN

LINKEDIN_ACCESS_TOKEN=your-access-token-here
LINKEDIN_PERSON_URN=your-person-urn-here

# -------------------------------------------
# Vault Configuration
# -------------------------------------------

VAULT_PATH=./AI_Employee_Vault

# -------------------------------------------
# Optional: Webhook URLs for notifications
# -------------------------------------------

# Slack webhook for notifications
# SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL=https://hooks.slack.com/services/YOUR/WEBHOOK/URL

# Discord webhook for notifications
# DISCORD_WEBHOOK_URL=https://discord.com/api/webhooks/YOUR/WEBHOOK

# -------------------------------------------
# Development Mode
# -------------------------------------------
# Set to 'true' to prevent actual actions (testing)

DRY_RUN=false

```

## Setup Instructions

### 1. Gmail API Setup

1. Go to [Google Cloud Console](https://console.cloud.google.com/)
2. Create a new project or select existing
3. Enable Gmail API
4. Create OAuth 2.0 credentials (Desktop app)
5. Download `credentials.json`
6. Place in `scripts/` folder
7. Run `python gmail_watcher.py ../AI_Employee_Vault` to authorize

### 2. Gmail App Password

1. Go to [Google Account](https://myaccount.google.com/)
2. Security → 2-Step Verification
3. App passwords → Generate new app password
4. Copy the 16-character password
5. Use in `.env` file as `SMTP_PASS`

### 3. LinkedIn API Setup

1. Go to [LinkedIn Developer Portal](https://www.linkedin.com/developers/)
2. Create a new app
3. Get access token (Sign In with LinkedIn using OpenID Connect)
4. Get your person URN from the API response
5. Add to `.env` file

### 4. WhatsApp Web

1. Run `python whatsapp_watcher.py ../AI_Employee_Vault`
2. Browser will open with QR code
3. Scan QR code with WhatsApp mobile app
4. Session saved automatically

## Verification

Run this command to verify setup:

```bash
cd scripts
python -c "from dotenv import load_dotenv; load_dotenv(); import os; print('Environment loaded successfully')"
```

## Security Notes

- ⚠️ **NEVER** commit `.env` file to git
- ⚠️ **NEVER** share your credentials
- ⚠️ Rotate passwords monthly
- ✅ Use app-specific passwords
- ✅ Enable 2FA on all accounts

## Troubleshooting

### Gmail API Error
- Check credentials.json is in `scripts/` folder
- Re-run authorization: delete `token.json` and run watcher again

### WhatsApp Not Connecting
- Delete session folder and re-authenticate
- Check internet connection
- Wait 60 seconds between attempts

### Email Not Sending
- Verify SMTP credentials in `.env`
- Test connection: `node mcp-servers/email-mcp/email_mcp.js` then use test_connection tool
- Check spam folder for sent emails

